orm of   Isabel   and related names (the mining centre of Mount Isa in Queensland, Australia, was named by the prospector  John Campbell Miles  after his sister  Isabella ), but now more commonly used as an independent first name, pronounced ‘<b>eye</b>-za’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Mael Isu Strathearn Earl of Strathearn was born in 1099, in Ruthven, Angus, Scotland, United Kingdom, his father, Forteith of Strathearn, was 29 and his mother, MacDonald, was 30. He had at least 1 son with Rosabel Strathearn. He died after 14 June 1141."},"et":{"1099–Aft 14 June 1141":"1099–pärast 14. juunit 1141","1099–1141":"1099–1141","1090–1180":"1090–1180","1125–1170":"1125–1170","1070–1150":"1070–1150","1070–Female":"1070–Surnud","1090":"1090","1138":"1138","1125":"1125","Aft 14 June 1141":"pärast 14. juunit 1141","1099":"1099","1141":"1141","1150":"1150","1170":"1170","1070":"1070","1180":"1180","Central, Renfrewshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Renfrewshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Ruthven, Angus, Scotland":"Ruthven, Angus, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Ruthven, Perth, Scotland":"Ruthven, Perthshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fi":{"1099–Aft 14 June 1141":"1099–14. kesäkuuta 1141 jälkeen","1099–1141":"1099–1141","1090–1180":"1090–1180","1125–1170":"1125–1170","1070–1150":"1070–1150","1070–Female":"1070–Kuollut","1090":"1090","1138":"1138","1125":"1125","Aft 14 June 1141":"14. kesäkuuta 1141 jälkeen","1099":"1099","1141":"1141","1150":"1150","1170":"1170","1070":"1070","1180":"1180","Central, Renfrewshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Renfrewshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Ruthven, Angus, Scotland":"Ruthven, Angus, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Ruthven, Perth, Scotland":"Ruthven, Perthshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fr":{"1099–Aft 14 June 1141":"1099–après 14 juin 1141","1099–1141":"1099–1141","1090–1180":"1090–1180","1125–1170":"1125–1170","1070–1150":"1070–1150","1070–Female":"1070–Décédée",